column10: These are all great people. Explorers. Adventurers.
column17: I’ll have these records for now – I will be able to easily add additional entries after I’ve written up my program!

column1:
Reached by Senior Lieutenant Yuri Alexeyevich 
Gagarin in the flight that sent man into space for 
the first time in history. He travelled aboard the 
Vostok 1 spacecraft and spent one day in space.
column2:
Gemini 11 crew Charles Conrad, Jr and Richard F. 
Gordon, Jr. fired their Agena Target Vehicle ro-
cket engine on 14 September 1966, at 40 hours 30 
minutes after liftoff and chieved a record apogee 
altitude of 1,369 km. This altitude record was held 
prior to lunar missions.
column3:
Apollo 13 crew; Jim Lovell, Fred Haise, Jack Swi-
gert while passing over the far side of the moon 
at an altitude of 254 km from the lunar surface, 
were 400,171 km from Earth.
column4:
The International Space Station begins construc-
tion. Sixteen countries are involved in the project.
column5:
Elon musk sends humans to Mars for the first time 
in human history, in SpaceX’s BFR rocket.
